erface -v`\n35: \n36: ### Phase 2: Config & Constants (ST-2)\n37: \n38: - [x] **T2.1**: Define `Config` struct in `config.go`\n39:   - `Port string` (default \":8080\")\n40:   - `EnableTLS bool`\n41:   - `TLSCert string`\n42:   - `TLSKey string`\n43:   - `MaxConcurrentRequests int` (default 1000)\n44:   - `Debug bool`\n45:   - File: `pkg/router/config.go`\n46:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestConfig -v`\n47: \n48: - [x] **T2.2**: Implement `DefaultConfig()` function\n49:   - Returns `Config{Port: \":8080\", EnableTLS: false, MaxConcurrentRequests: 1000}`\n50:   - File: `pkg/router/config.go`\n51:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewServerNilConfig -v`\n52: \n53: - [x] **T2.3**: Define constants in `jwt.go`\n54:   - `rsaKeySize = 2048`\n55:   - `jwtExpiration = 5 * time.Minute`\n56:   - `IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"`\n57:   - `PrivateKeyDataKey = \"private.pem\"`\n58:   - `PublicKeyDataKey = \"public.pem\"`\n59:   - `IdentityNamespace = \"default\"` (overridden by AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE env)\n60:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n61:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerTokenExpiration -v`\n62: \n63: ### Phase 3: Interfaces (ST-3)\n64: \n65: - [x] **T3.1**: Define `Store` interface in `doc.go`\n66:   - `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n67:   - `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error`\n68:   - `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at) error`\n69:   - File: `pkg/router/doc.go`\n70:   - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n71: \n72: - [x] **T3.2**: Define `Logger` interface in `doc.go`\n73:   - Methods: `Info(msg, keysAndValues...)`, `Error(msg, keysAndValues...)`, `Warning(msg, keysAndValues...)`\n74:   - File: `pkg/router/doc.go`\n75:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestLoggingMiddleware -v`\n76: \n77: - [x] **T3.3**: Define `SessionManager` interface in `doc.go`\n78:   - `GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n79:   - File: `pkg/router/doc.go`\n80:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSessionManager -v`\n81: \n82: - [x] **T3.4**: Define `JWTManagerInterface` interface in `doc.go`\n83:   - `GenerateToken(claims) (string, error)`\n84:   - `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx) error`\n85:   - File: `pkg/router/doc.go`\n86:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManager -v`\n87: \n88: ### Phase 4: JWTManager Implementation (ST-4)\n89: \n90: - [x] **T4.1**: Implement `JWTManager` struct\n91:   - `privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey`\n92:   - `publicKey *rsa.PublicKey`\n93:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n94:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewJWTManager -v`\n95: \n96: - [x] **T4.2**: Implement RSA key generation\n97:   - `rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, 2048)` in `NewJWTManager()`\n98:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n99:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerGetPublicKey -v`\n100: \n101: - [x] **T4.3**: Implement PEM encoding helpers\n102:   - `encodePrivateKeyPEM(key)` - PKCS1 PEM encoding\n103:   - `encodePublicKeyPEM(key)` - PKIX PEM encoding\n104:   - `loadPrivateKeyPEM(data)` - Parse PKCS1 PEM\n105:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n106:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestEncodePrivateKeyPEM -v`\n107: \n108: - [x] **T4.4**: Implement `GenerateToken(claims)` method\n109:   - Create JWT with claims: `exp` (now+5m), `iat` (now), `iss=\"agentcube-router\"`\n110:   - Merge custom claims into token\n111:   - Sign with RS256 algorithm\n112:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n113:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerGenerateToken -v`\n114: \n115: - [x] **T4.5**: Implement `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx)` method\n116:   - Placeholder for in-cluster secret persistence\n117:   - Returns warning when not in cluster\n118:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n119:   - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n120: \n121: - [x] **T4.6**: Implement `GetPublicKey()` method\n122:   - Returns `*rsa.PublicKey` for token verification\n123:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n124:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerGetPublicKey -v`\n125: \n126: ### Phase 5: SessionManager Implementation (ST-5)\n127: \n128: - [x] **T5.1**: Implement `sessionManager` struct\n129:   - `storeClient Store`\n130:   - `workloadMgrAddr string`\n131:   - `httpClient *http.Client`\n132:   - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n133:   - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n134: \n135: - [x] **T5.2**: Implement `NewSessionManager(store)` constructor\n136:   - Read `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env var (required, fail if missing)\n137:   - Configure HTTP client: `Timeout=2m`, HTTP2 enabled\n138:   - `MaxIdleConnsPerHost=100`\n139:   - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n140:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewSessionManagerRequiresWorkloadManagerURL -v`\n141: \n142: - [x] **T5.3**: Implement `GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)` method\n143:   - If `sessionID` empty: call `createSandbox(ctx, namespace, name, kind)`\n144:   - If `sessionID` present: call `storeClient.GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)`\n145:   - Return `SandboxInfo` or `SessionNotFoundError`\n146:   - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n147:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSessionManagerGetSandboxBySessionWithExistingSession -v`\n148: \n149: - [x] **T5.4**: Implement `createSandbox(ctx, namespace, name, kind)` internal method\n150:   - Build `CreateSandboxRequest` with Kind, Name, Namespace\n151:   - POST to `/v1/agent-runtime` for `AgentRuntimeKind`\n152:   - POST to `/v1/code-interpreter` for `CodeInterpreterKind`\n153:   - Add K8s SA token via `readServiceAccountToken()` if available\n154:   - Parse `CreateSandboxResponse` and store via `StoreSandbox`\n155:   - Set `ExpiresAt` to `CreatedAt + 30min`\n156:   - Return error for unsupported kind\n157:   - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n158:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSessionManagerCreateSandbox -v`\n159: \n160: - [x] **T5.5**: Implement `readServiceAccountToken()` helper\n161:   - Read from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n162:   - Return trimmed token string\n163:   - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n164:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestReadServiceAccountToken -v`\n165: \n166: ### Phase 6: Middleware Implementation (ST-6)\n167: \n168: - [x] **T6.1**: Implement `concurrencyLimitMiddleware(maxConcurrent)` function\n169:   - Use buffered channel as semaphore\n170:   - Capacity = `maxConcurrent` (default 1000 if <=0)\n171:   - `sem <- struct{}{}` to acquire slot (deferred release)\n172:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n173:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestConcurrencyLimitMiddlewareUnderLimit -v`\n174: \n175: - [x] **T6.2**: Implement 429 overload response\n176:   - `select` with `default` case when semaphore full\n177:   - Return HTTP 429 with `{\"error\": \"server overloaded\", \"code\": \"SERVER_OVERLOADED\"}`\n178:   - Call `c.Abort()` to stop processing\n179:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n180:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestConcurrencyLimitMiddlewareOverLimit -v`\n181: \n182: - [x] **T6.3**: Implement `loggingMiddleware(logger)` function\n183:   - Log request method, path, status, duration\n184:   - Use `logger.Info(\"request\", ...)` with keys\n185:   - Handle nil logger gracefully\n186:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n187:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestLoggingMiddleware -v`\n188: \n189: - [x] **T6.4**: Implement `recoveryMiddleware(logger)` function\n190:   - Recover from panics with `defer`\n191:   - Log error with path, method\n192:   - Return HTTP 500 with `{\"error\": \"internal server error\"}`\n193:   - Call `c.Abort()`\n194:   - Handle nil logger gracefully\n195:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n196:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestRecoveryMiddleware -v`\n197: \n198: ### Phase 7: Reverse Proxy Implementation (ST-7)\n199: \n200: - [x] **T7.1**: Implement `ReverseProxyWrapper` struct\n201:   - `director func(*http.Request)`\n202:   - `modifyResponse func(*http.Response) error`\n203:   - `errorHandler func(http.ResponseWriter, *http.Request, error)`\n204:   - Methods: `Director()`, `ModifyResponse()`, `ErrorHandler()`\n205:   - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n206:   - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n207: \n208: - [x] **T7.2**: Implement `newReverseProxy(target, jwt, sessionID)` function\n209:   - Create `ReverseProxyWrapper` with configured functions\n210:   - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n211:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestReverseProxy -v`\n212: \n213: - [x] **T7.3**: Implement `Director` function\n214:   - Path normalization: add leading `/` if missing\n215:   - Set `req.URL.Scheme`, `req.URL.Host`, `req.URL.Path`\n216:   - Set `req.Host` to target host\n217:   - Set forwarding headers: `X-Forwarded-Host`, `X-Forwarded-Proto`, `X-Forwarded-For`\n218:   - Inject JWT: `Authorization: Bearer <jwt>` if jwt non-empty\n219:   - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n220:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestBuildTargetURL -v`\n221: \n222: - [x] **T7.4**: Implement `ModifyResponse` function\n223:   - Add `x-agentcube-session-id` header to response\n224:   - Value is the resolved session ID\n225:   - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n226:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestReverseProxy -v`\n227: \n228: - [x] **T7.5**: Implement `ErrorHandler` function\n229:   - Check for \"connection refused\" → HTTP 502 `sandbox unreachable`\n230:   - Check for \"timeout\" → HTTP 504 `sandbox timeout`\n231:   - Other errors → HTTP 502\n232:   - Return JSON response: `{\"error\": \"<message>\"}`\n233:   - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n234:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestReverseProxy -v`\n235: \n236: - [x] **T7.6**: Implement `selectEntryPoint(entryPoints, invocationPath)` helper\n237:   - Find matching entry point by path prefix (HasPrefix)\n238:   - Default to first entry point if no match\n239:   - Return nil if `entryPoints` is empty\n240:   - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n241:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSelectEntryPoint -v`\n242: \n243: - [x] **T7.7**: Implement `buildTargetURL(entryPoint)` helper\n244:   - Parse `entryPoint.Endpoint` as URL\n245:   - Add protocol prefix if missing: `entryPoint.Protocol + \"://\" + endpoint`\n246:   - Return parsed `url.URL`\n247:   - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n248:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestBuildTargetURL -v`\n249: \n250: ### Phase 8: Server & Handlers Implementation (ST-8)\n251: \n252: - [x] **T8.1**: Implement `Server` struct\n253:   - `config *Config`\n254:   - `engine *gin.Engine`\n255:   - `httpServer *http.Server`\n256:   - `sessionManager SessionManager`\n257:   - `storeClient Store`\n258:   - `httpTransport *http.Transport`\n259:   - `jwtManager *JWTManager`\n260:   - `logger Logger`\n261:   - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n262:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewServer -v`\n263: \n264: - [x] **T8.2**: Implement `NewServer(config, sessionManager, store, jwtManager, logger)` constructor\n265:   - Create `engine := gin.New()`\n266:   - Set Gin mode: `gin.ReleaseMode` if `!config.Debug`\n267:   - Initialize `httpTransport` with `MaxIdleConnsPerHost=100`\n268:   - Configure `httpServer` with `ReadTimeout=30s`, `IdleTimeout=90s`\n269:   - Set default `MaxConcurrentRequests=1000` if <=0\n270:   - Register routes via `registerRoutes()`\n271:   - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n272:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewServer -v`\n273: \n274: - [x] **T8.3**: Implement route registration in `registerRoutes()`\n275:   - `/health/live` → `handleHealthLive` (no middleware)\n276:   - `/health/ready` → `handleHealthReady` (no middleware)\n277:   - `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` → `handleAgentInvoke` (GET, POST)\n278:   - `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` → `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` (GET, POST)\n279:   - Apply middleware: `concurrencyLimitMiddleware`, `loggingMiddleware`, `recoveryMiddleware`\n280:   - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n281:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServerRoutesRegistered -v`\n282: \n283: - [x] **T8.4**: Implement `handleHealthLive(c)` handler\n284:   - Return HTTP 200\n285:   - Body: `{\"status\": \"alive\"}`\n286:   - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n287:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServerHandleHealthLive -v`\n288: \n289: - [x] **T8.5**: Implement `handleHealthReady(c)` handler\n290:   - Check if `sessionManager != nil`\n291:   - If nil: HTTP 503, body: `{\"status\": \"not ready\", \"error\": \"session manager not available\"}`\n292:   - If valid: HTTP 200, body: `{\"status\": \"ready\"}`\n293:   - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n294:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServerHandleHealthReady -v`\n295: \n296: - [x] **T8.6**: Implement `handleAgentInvoke(c)` handler\n297:   - Set `kind = AgentRuntimeKind`\n298:   - Delegate to `handleInvoke(c, kind)`\n299:   - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n300:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServerHandleAgentInvoke -v`\n301: \n302: - [x] **T8.7**: Implement `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke(c)` handler\n303:   - Set `kind = CodeInterpreterKind`\n304:   - Delegate to `handleInvoke(c, kind)`\n305:   - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n306:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServerHandleCodeInterpreterInvoke -v`\n307: \n308: - [x] **T8.8**: Implement `handleInvoke(c, kind)` handler\n309:   - Extract `namespace`, `name` from URL path params\n310:   - Extract `invocationPath` from wildcard param\n311:   - Extract `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n312:   - Call `sessionManager.GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)`\n313:   - Check for empty `EntryPoints` → 404 `NO_ENTRY_POINT`\n314:   - Update activity via `storeClient.UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, time.Now())`\n315:   - Select entry point via `selectEntryPoint(entryPoints, invocationPath)`\n316:   - Build target URL via `buildTargetURL(entryPoint)`\n317:   - Generate JWT for `SandboxKind`/`SandboxClaimKind` only\n318:   - Create reverse proxy with `newReverseProxy(target, jwt, sessionID)`\n319:   - Serve HTTP via `proxy.ServeHTTP(c.Writer, c.Request)`\n320:   - Update activity again after proxy\n321:   - Handle errors via `handleGetSandboxError(c, err)`\n322:   - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n323:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestHandleInvoke -v`\n324: \n325: - [x] **T8.9**: Implement `handleGetSandboxError(c, err)` helper\n326:   - Check `apierrors.IsNotFound(err)` → HTTP 404\n327:   - Check `apierrors.APIStatus` → use status code from APIStatus\n328:   - Check router `APIStatus` → use `Status()`, `Code()`, `Message()`\n329:   - Other errors → HTTP 500 with `\"internal server error\"`\n330:   - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n331:   - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n332: \n333: - [x] **T8.10**: Implement `Start(ctx)` method\n334:   - If `EnableTLS`: check cert/key not empty, call `ListenAndServeTLS`\n335:   - If not TLS: call `ListenAndServe()`\n336:   - Launch goroutine for `waitForShutdown(ctx)`\n337:   - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n338:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServerTLSRequired -v`\n339: \n340: - [x] **T8.11**: Implement `waitForShutdown(ctx)` method\n341:   - Wait for `ctx.Done()`\n342:   - Create shutdown context with 10s timeout\n343:   - Call `httpServer.Shutdown(shutdownCtx)`\n344:   - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n345:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServerGracefulShutdown -v`\n346: \n347: - [x] **T8.12**: Implement `Stop()` method\n348:   - Create context with 10s timeout\n349:   - Call `httpServer.Shutdown(ctx)`\n350:   - Return error\n351:   - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n352:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServerStop -v`\n353: \n354: - [x] **T8.13**: Implement `GetEngine()` method\n355:   - Return `*gin.Engine` for testing access\n356:   - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n357:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServerGetEngine -v`\n358: \n359: ### Phase 9: Mock Implementations for Testing (ST-9)\n360: \n361: - [x] **T9.1**: Implement `MockStore` in test files\n362:   - `GetSandboxBySessionIDFunc func(ctx, sessionID) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n363:   - `StoreSandboxFunc func(ctx, sandbox) error`\n364:   - `UpdateSessionLastActivityFunc func(ctx, sessionID, at) error`\n365:   - File: `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go`\n366:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestMockStore -v`\n367: \n368: - [x] **T9.2**: Implement `MockLogger` in test files\n369:   - `InfoCalls []string`\n370:   - `ErrorCalls []string`\n371:   - `WarningCalls []string`\n372:   - Methods record calls for verification\n373:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware_test.go`\n374:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestMockLogger -v`\n375: \n376: - [x] **T9.3**: Implement `mockSessionManager` in test files\n377:   - `getFunc func(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n378:   - Implements `SessionManager` interface\n379:   - File: `pkg/router/server_test.go`\n380:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestMockSessionManager -v`\n381: \n382: - [x] **T9.4**: Implement `MockHTTPClient` in test files\n383:   - `DoFunc func(req) (*http.Response, error)`\n384:   - File: `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go`\n385:   - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n386: \n387: ### Phase 10: Validation & Coverage (ST-10)\n388: \n389: - [x] **T10.1**: All unit tests pass\n390:   - `go test ./pkg/router -v`\n391:   - File: `pkg/router/*_test.go`\n392:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -v`\n393: \n394: - [x] **T10.2**: Verify error type tests pass\n395:   - `SessionNotFoundError`, `SandboxUnreachableError`, etc.\n396:   - File: `pkg/router/errors_test.go`\n397:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestError -v`\n398: \n399: - [x] **T10.3**: Verify config tests pass\n400:   - `DefaultConfig`, nil config handling\n401:   - File: `pkg/router/config_test.go`\n402:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestConfig -v`\n403: \n404: - [x] **T10.4**: Verify JWT tests pass\n405:   - Token generation, expiration, PEM encoding\n406:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n407:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManager -v`\n408: \n409: - [x] **T10.5**: Verify session manager tests pass\n410:   - NewSessionManager, GetSandboxBySession, createSandbox\n411:   - File: `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go`\n412:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSessionManager -v`\n413: \n414: - [x] **T10.6**: Verify middleware tests pass\n415:   - Concurrency limit, logging, recovery\n416:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware_test.go`\n417:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestMiddleware -v`\n418: \n419: - [x] **T10.7**: Verify reverse proxy tests pass\n420:   - selectEntryPoint, buildTargetURL\n421:   - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go`\n422:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestReverseProxy -v`\n423: \n424: - [x] **T10.8**: Verify server tests pass\n425:   - NewServer, health handlers, routes, shutdown\n426:   - File: `pkg/router/server_test.go`\n427:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServer -v`\n428: \n429: ---\n430: \n431: ## Task Dependencies\n432: \n433: ```\n434: T1.1 ──── T1.2\n435:   │\n436:   ▼\n437: T2.1 ──── T2.2 ──── T2.3\n438:   │\n439:   ▼\n440: T3.1 ──── T3.2 ──── T3.3 ──── T3.4\n441:   │\n442:   ▼\n443: T4.1 ──── T4.2 ──── T4.3 ──── T4.4 ──── T4.5 ──── T4.6\n444:   │\n445:   ▼\n446: T5.1 ──── T5.2 ──── T5.3 ──── T5.4 ──── T5.5\n447:   │\n448:   ▼\n449: T6.1 ──── T6.2 ──── T6.3 ──── T6.4\n450:   │\n451:   ▼\n452: T7.1 ──── T7.2 ──── T7.3 ──── T7.4 ──── T7.5 ──── T7.6 ──── T7.7\n453:   │\n454:   ▼\n455: T8.1 ──── T8.2 ──── T8.3 ──── T8.4 ──── T8.5 ──── T8.6 ──── T8.7 ──── T8.8 ──── T8.9 ──── T8.10 ──── T8.11 ──── T8.12 ──── T8.13\n456:   │\n457:   ▼\n458: T9.1 ──── T9.2 ──── T9.3 ──── T9.4\n459:   │\n460:   ▼\n461: T10.1 ──── T10.2 ──── T10.3 ──── T10.4 ──── T10.5 ──── T10.6 ──── T10.7 ──── T10.8\n462: ```\n463: \n464: ---\n465: \n466: ## Verification Commands\n467: \n468: | Task | Verification Command |\n469: |------|----------------------|\n470: | All router tests | `go test ./pkg/router -v` |\n471: | Error types tests | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestError -v` |\n472: | Config tests | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestConfig -v` |\n473: | JWT tests | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManager -v` |\n474: | Session manager tests | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSessionManager -v` |\n475: | Middleware tests | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestMiddleware -v` |\n476: | Reverse proxy tests | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestReverseProxy -v` |\n477: | Server tests | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServer -v` |\n478: | Build verification | `go build ./pkg/router/...` |\n479: | Package vet | `go vet ./pkg/router/...` |\n480: \n481: ---\n482: \n483: ## Acceptance Criteria\n484: \n485: - [x] Server struct defined with all required fields\n486: - [x] Config struct with Port, TLS, MaxConcurrentRequests, Debug\n487: - [x] NewServer constructor initializes Gin engine\n488: - [x] Gin mode set based on Debug config\n489: - [x] Server.Start supports TLS and non-TLS\n490: - [x] Graceful shutdown with 10s deadline\n491: - [x] Health routes registered (/health/live, /health/ready)\n492: - [x] Invocation routes registered with GET and POST\n493: - [x] Middleware chain applied (concurrency, logging, recovery)\n494: - [x] SessionManager interface defined\n495: - [x] GetSandboxBySession resolves or creates sessions\n496: - [x] createSandbox POST to Workload Manager\n497: - [x] K8s SA token added for in-cluster auth\n498: - [x] ReverseProxyWrapper with Director, ModifyResponse, ErrorHandler\n499: - [x] Director normalizes path and injects JWT\n500: - [x] ModifyResponse adds session header\n501: - [x] ErrorHandler maps errors to HTTP codes (502/504)\n502: - [x] JWTManager with RSA key generation\n503: - [x] GenerateToken with RS256, 5m expiration\n504: - [x] TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret placeholder\n505: - [x] concurrencyLimitMiddleware with semaphore\n506: - [x] 429 returned when overloaded\n507: - [x] handleHealthLive returns 200 {\"status\":\"alive\"}\n508: - [x] handleHealthReady checks sessionManager availability\n509: - [x] handleInvoke proxies to sandbox with activity tracking\n510: - [x] Activity timestamp updated before and after proxy\n511: - [x] Error types implement APIStatus interface\n512: - [x] WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL required for SessionManager\n513: - [x] AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE with default \"default\"\n514: - [x] Constants defined (rsaKeySize, jwtExpiration, IdentitySecretName)\n515: - [x] Unit tests for all components\n516: - [x] Mock implementations for testing\n517: \n518: ---\n519: \n520: ## Files Modified/Created\n521: \n522: | File | Status | Description |\n523: |------|--------|-------------|\n524: | `pkg/router/errors.go` | Created | Error types with APIStatus interface |\n525: | `pkg/router/errors_test.go` | Created | Error types unit tests |\n526: | `pkg/router/config.go` | Created | Config struct and DefaultConfig |\n527: | `pkg/router/config_test.go` | Created | Config unit tests |\n528: | `pkg/router/doc.go` | Created | Interface definitions (Store, Logger, SessionManager, APIStatus) |\n529: | `pkg/router/jwt.go` | Created | JWTManager implementation with RS256 |\n530: | `pkg/router/jwt_test.go` | Created | JWT unit tests |\n531: | `pkg/router/session_manager.go` | Created | SessionManager implementation |\n532: | `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go` | Created | SessionManager unit tests with MockStore |\n533: | `pkg/router/middleware.go` | Created | Concurrency, logging, recovery middleware |\n534: | `pkg/router/middleware_test.go` | Created | Middleware unit tests with MockLogger |\n535: | `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go` | Created | Reverse proxy with Director, ModifyResponse, ErrorHandler |\n536: | `pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go` | Created | Reverse proxy unit tests |\n537: | `pkg/router/server.go` | Created | HTTP Server with Gin engine, handlers, shutdown |\n538: | `pkg/router/server_test.go` | Created | Server unit tests with mockSessionManager |\n539: \n540: ---\n541: \n542: ## Notes\n543: \n544: - **Design completed at Stage ST-3**\n545: - **Implementation completed**\n546: - **Dependencies**:\n547:   - `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` - HTTP framework\n548:   - `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` - JWT signing\n549:   - `golang.org/x/net/http2` - HTTP/2 transport\n550:   - `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` - APIStatus interface\n551:   - `k8s.io/klog/v2` - Logging\n552:   - `pkg/common/types` - SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response\n553: - **Environment Variables**:\n554:   - `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` (required) - Workload Manager endpoint\n555:   - `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (optional, default \"default\") - Router identity namespace\n556: \n557: ---\n558: \n559: ## Implementation Timeline\n560: \n561: | Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n562: |-------|-------|--------|------------|\n563: | Phase 1: Error Types & Interfaces | T1.1, T1.2 | Completed | 100% |\n564: | Phase 2: Config & Constants | T2.1-T2.3 | Completed | 100% |\n565: | Phase 3: Interfaces | T3.1-T3.4 | Completed | 100% |\n566: | Phase 4: JWTManager | T4.1-T4.6 | Completed | 100% |\n567: | Phase 5: SessionManager | T5.1-T5.5 | Completed | 100% |\n568: | Phase 6: Middleware | T6.1-T6.4 | Completed | 100% |\n569: | Phase 7: Reverse Proxy | T7.1-T7.7 | Completed | 100% |\n570: | Phase 8: Server & Handlers | T8.1-T8.13 | Completed | 100% |\n571: | Phase 9: Mock Implementations | T9.1-T9.4 | Completed | 100% |\n572: | Phase 10: Validation & Coverage | T10.1-T10.8 | Completed | 100% |\n573: \n574: **Total Progress: 100% Complete (53/53 tasks)**\n\n