{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851879392,"sessionID":"ses_286fb3a50ffevXBFaIE185eANl","part":{"id":"prt_d7905375d0010Qx69HBliD2aVR","messageID":"msg_d790513b70017BHPjMM1eOOInL","sessionID":"ses_286fb3a50ffevXBFaIE185eANl","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-91e0229a46d24430bb2db7050324d6ef","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-010/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-010/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-010 — Router 会话管理 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-010 — Router 会话管理 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/router` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: The Router module provides HTTP-based session routing for AgentCube sandboxes. It manages session lifecycle, routes incoming invocation requests to appropriate sandbox pods via reverse proxy, and handles JWT-based authentication for secure communication between Router and Workload Manager.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Architecture\n18: \n19: ### System Context\n20: \n21: ```\n22: ┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n23: │   Client SDK    │────▶│     Router      │────▶│  WorkloadMgr    │\n24: │ (Python/CLI)    │     │  (pkg/router)   │     │(pkg/workloadmgr)│\n25: └─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n26:                               │                         │\n27:                               │                         │\n28:                               ▼                         ▼\n29:                         ┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n30:                         │   Session Store │     │   Kubernetes    │\n31:                         │ (Redis/Memory)  │     │   API Server    │\n32:                         └─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n33: ```\n34: \n35: ### Request Flow\n36: \n37: ```\n38: Client Request (with x-agentcube-session-id header)\n39:        │\n40:        ▼\n41: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n42: │ 1. Concurrency Limit Middleware (semaphore channel)      │\n43: │    - Reject with 429 if max concurrent exceeded          │\n44: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n45:        │\n46:        ▼\n47: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n48: │ 2. Logging Middleware                                    │\n49: │    - Record request method, path, duration               │\n50: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n51:        │\n52:        ▼\n53: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n54: │ 3. Recovery Middleware                                   │\n55: │    - Panic recovery → 500 response                       │\n56: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n57:        │\n58:        ▼\n59: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n60: │ 4. handleInvoke (AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter)           │\n61: │    - Extract namespace, name, path from URL params       │\n62: │    - Get sessionID from x-agentcube-session-id header    │\n63: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n64:        │\n65:        ▼\n66: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n67: │ 5. SessionManager.GetSandboxBySession                    │\n68: │    - If sessionID empty → create new sandbox             │\n69: │    - If sessionID provided → lookup from store           │\n70: │    - On not found → SessionNotFoundError                 │\n71: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n72:        │\n73:        ▼\n74: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n75: │ 6. UpdateSessionLastActivity (before proxy)              │\n76: │    - Update LastActivity timestamp in store              │\n77: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n78:        │\n79:        ▼\n80: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n81: │ 7. Entry Point Selection                                 │\n82: │    - selectEntryPoint: prefix match or first entry       │\n83: │    - buildTargetURL: construct backend URL               │\n84: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n85:        │\n86:        ▼\n87: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n88: │ 8. JWT Generation (for Sandbox/SandboxClaim kinds)       │\n89: │    - JWTManager.GenerateToken with session claims        │\n90: │    - RS256 signing with RSA 2048-bit key                 │\n91: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n92:        │\n93:        ▼\n94: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n95: │ 9. Reverse Proxy                                         │\n96: │    - httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy                  │\n97: │    - Director: rewrite URL, add forwarding headers       │\n98: │    - ModifyResponse: set x-agentcube-session-id          │\n99: │    - ErrorHandler: connection refused → 502, timeout→504│\n100: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n101:        │\n102:        ▼\n103: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n104: │ 10. UpdateSessionLastActivity (after proxy)              │\n105: │    - Update activity timestamp again                     │\n106: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n107: ```\n108: \n109: ---\n110: \n111: ## Design\n112: \n113: ### Component Relationships\n114: \n115: | Component | Role | Dependencies |\n116: |-----------|------|--------------|\n117: | `Server` | Gin HTTP server, route registration, graceful shutdown | `Config`, `SessionManager`, `Store`, `JWTManager`, `Logger` |\n118: | `sessionManager` | Session lookup, sandbox creation via Workload Manager | `Store`, `http.Client` (to WorkloadMgr) |\n119: | `JWTManager` | RS256 JWT token generation, key persistence | `rsa.PrivateKey`, Kubernetes client (optional) |\n120: | `ReverseProxyWrapper` | Request director, response modification, error handling | `url.URL`, JWT string |\n121: | `Store` (interface) | Session/sandbox CRUD, activity tracking | Redis or in-memory implementation |\n122: | `middleware.go` | Concurrency limiting, logging, panic recovery | `gin.Context`, `Logger` |\n123: | `errors.go` | Custom error types with APIStatus interface | None |\n124: \n125: ### Dependencies\n126: \n127: | Package | Purpose | Import Path |\n128: |---------|---------|-------------|\n129: | Gin | HTTP router and middleware | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` |\n130: | JWT | JWT token generation and signing | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` |\n131: | HTTP2 | HTTP/2 transport configuration | `golang.org/x/net/http2` |\n132: | Kubernetes API | APIStatus error interface | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` |\n133: | Klog | Logging | `k8s.io/klog/v2` |\n134: | Common Types | SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` |\n135: \n136: ---\n137: \n138: ## Data Structures\n139: \n140: ### Config (`config.go`)\n141: \n142: ```go\n143: type Config struct {\n144:     Port                  string  // Default \":8080\"\n145:     EnableTLS             bool    // TLS mode toggle\n146:     TLSCert               string  // TLS certificate file path\n147:     TLSKey                string  // TLS key file path\n148:     MaxConcurrentRequests int     // Semaphore size, default 1000\n149:     Debug                 bool    // Gin debug mode toggle\n150: }\n151: ```\n152: \n153: ### Server (`server.go`)\n154: \n155: ```go\n156: type Server struct {\n157:     config         *Config\n158:     engine         *gin.Engine\n159:     httpServer     *http.Server\n160:     sessionManager SessionManager\n161:     storeClient    Store\n162:     httpTransport  *http.Transport\n163:     jwtManager     *JWTManager\n164:     logger         Logger\n165: }\n166: ```\n167: \n168: ### sessionManager (`session_manager.go`)\n169: \n170: ```go\n171: type sessionManager struct {\n172:     storeClient     Store\n173:     workloadMgrAddr string         // From WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL env\n174:     httpClient      *http.Client   // Timeout: 2m, HTTP/2 enabled\n175: }\n176: ```\n177: \n178: ### JWTManager (`jwt.go`)\n179: \n180: ```go\n181: type JWTManager struct {\n182:     privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey  // 2048-bit RSA key\n183:     publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n184: }\n185: \n186: const (\n187:     rsaKeySize         = 2048\n188:     jwtExpiration      = 5 * time.Minute\n189:     IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"\n190:     PrivateKeyDataKey  = \"private.pem\"\n191:     PublicKeyDataKey   = \"public.pem\"\n192: )\n193: \n194: var IdentityNamespace = \"default\" // Overridden by AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\n195: ```\n196: \n197: ### SandboxInfo (`pkg/common/types/sandbox.go`)\n198: \n199: ```go\n200: type SandboxInfo struct {\n201:     Kind               string\n202:     SandboxID          string\n203:     SandboxNamespace   string\n204:     SandboxName        string\n205:     Name               string\n206:     SessionID          string\n207:     CreatedAt          time.Time\n208:     ExpiresAt          time.Time\n209:     Status             string\n210:     EntryPoints        []SandboxEntryPoint\n211:     UserToken          string              // Optional\n212:     ServiceAccount     string              // Optional\n213:     ServiceAccountName string              // Optional\n214:     LastActivity       time.Time           // Optional\n215: }\n216: \n217: type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n218:     Path     string  // URL path prefix\n219:     Protocol string  // \"http\" or \"https\"\n220:     Endpoint string  // Backend host:port or full URL\n221: }\n222: ```\n223: \n224: ### ReverseProxyWrapper (`reverse_proxy.go`)\n225: \n226: ```go\n227: type ReverseProxyWrapper struct {\n228:     director       func(*http.Request)\n229:     modifyResponse func(*http.Response) error\n230:     errorHandler   func(http.ResponseWriter, *http.Request, error)\n231: }\n232: ```\n233: \n234: ### Interfaces (`doc.go`)\n235: \n236: ```go\n237: type Store interface {\n238:     GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n239:     StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error\n240:     UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n241: }\n242: \n243: type Logger interface {\n244:     Info(msg string, keysAndValues ...any)\n245:     Error(msg string, keysAndValues ...any)\n246:     Warning(msg string, keysAndValues ...any)\n247: }\n248: \n249: type SessionManager interface {\n250:     GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace string, name string, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n251: }\n252: \n253: type APIStatus interface {\n254:     Status() int\n255:     Code() string\n256:     Message() string\n257: }\n258: ```\n259: \n260: ---\n261: \n262: ## API Contracts\n263: \n264: ### Route Table\n265: \n266: | Method | Path | Middleware | Handler |\n267: |--------|------|------------|---------|\n268: | GET | `/health/live` | none | `handleHealthLive` → `{\"status\":\"alive\"}` |\n269: | GET | `/health/ready` | none | `handleHealthReady` → `{\"status\":\"ready\"}` or 503 |\n270: | GET | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | concurrency, logging, recovery | `handleAgentInvoke` |\n271: | POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | concurrency, logging, recovery | `handleAgentInvoke` |\n272: | GET | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | concurrency, logging, recovery | `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` |\n273: | POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | concurrency, logging, recovery | `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` |\n274: \n275: ### Request Headers\n276: \n277: | Header | Required | Description |\n278: |--------|----------|-------------|\n279: | `x-agentcube-session-id` | No | Existing session ID for reuse; empty → new session creation |\n280: \n281: ### Response Headers\n282: \n283: | Header | Description |\n284: |--------|-------------|\n285: | `x-agentcube-session-id` | Session ID echoed back for client tracking |\n286: \n287: ### Workload Manager API Calls\n288: \n289: | Endpoint | Method | Request Body | Response |\n290: |----------|--------|--------------|----------|\n291: | `{WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/agent-runtime` | POST | `CreateSandboxRequest{kind, name, namespace}` | `CreateSandboxResponse{sessionId, sandboxId, sandboxName, entryPoints}` |\n292: | `{WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/code-interpreter` | POST | `CreateSandboxRequest{kind, name, namespace}` | `CreateSandboxResponse{sessionId, sandboxId, sandboxName, entryPoints}` |\n293: \n294: ### JWT Claims Structure\n295: \n296: ```json\n297: {\n298:   \"exp\": <unix timestamp + 5min>,\n299:   \"iat\": <unix timestamp>,\n300:   \"iss\": \"agentcube-router\",\n301:   \"session_id\": \"<session ID>\",\n302:   \"sandbox_id\": \"<sandbox ID>\",\n303:   \"namespace\": \"<sandbox namespace>\",\n304:   \"name\": \"<sandbox name>\"\n305: }\n306: ```\n307: \n308: ---\n309: \n310: ## Error Handling\n311: \n312: ### Custom Error Types (`errors.go`)\n313: \n314: | Error Type | HTTP Status | Code | Message |\n315: |------------|-------------|------|---------|\n316: | `SessionNotFoundError` | 404 | `SESSION_NOT_FOUND` | \"session not found\" |\n317: | `SandboxUnreachableError` | 502 | `SANDBOX_UNREACHABLE` | \"sandbox unreachable\" |\n318: | `SandboxTimeoutError` | 504 | `SANDBOX_TIMEOUT` | \"sandbox timeout\" |\n319: | `JWTSigningError` | 500 | `JWT_SIGNING_FAILED` | \"jwt signing failed\" |\n320: | `ServerOverloadedError` | 429 | `SERVER_OVERLOADED` | \"server overloaded, please try again later\" |\n321: | `NoEntryPointError` | 404 | `NO_ENTRY_POINT` | \"no entry point configured\" |\n322: | `WorkloadManagerError` | Dynamic | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_ERROR` | Dynamic message |\n323: \n324: ### Error Response Format\n325: \n326: ```json\n327: {\n328:   \"error\": \"<message>\",\n329:   \"code\": \"<error code>\"\n330: }\n331: ```\n332: \n333: ### Error Handling Strategy\n334: \n335: 1. **Session lookup errors**: Return `SessionNotFoundError` when session ID provided but not found in store\n336: 2. **Workload Manager errors**: Wrap HTTP response errors in `WorkloadManagerError` with original status code\n337: 3. **Proxy errors**: Detect \"connection refused\" → 502, \"timeout\" → 504 via string matching\n338: 4. **Entry point errors**: Return 404 if no entry points configured or path prefix not matched\n339: 5. **Concurrency limit**: Return 429 immediately when semaphore full (non-blocking)\n340: \n341: ---\n342: \n343: ## Testing Strategy\n344: \n345: ### Test Coverage Goals\n346: \n347: | Component | Coverage Target | Key Test Cases |\n348: |-----------|-----------------|----------------|\n349: | `session_manager.go` | 90%+ | Existing session lookup, new sandbox creation, WorkloadMgr errors, unsupported kind, empty sessionID in response |\n350: | `server.go` | 85%+ | Route registration, health endpoints, concurrent request limiting, TLS validation, graceful shutdown |\n351: | `jwt.go` | 80%+ | Token generation, claim merging, RSA key creation, PEM encoding/decoding |\n352: | `reverse_proxy.go` | 85%+ | Entry point selection, URL building, proxy director, error handler classification |\n353: | `middleware.go` | 90%+ | Concurrency limit (accept/reject), logging capture, panic recovery |\n354: | `errors.go` | 100% | All error type methods (Error, Status, Code, Message) |\n355: \n356: ### Test Patterns\n357: \n358: 1. **Mock Store**: `MockStore` with function fields for flexible testing\n359: 2. **Mock HTTP Client**: `httptest.Server` for Workload Manager simulation\n360: 3. **Mock SessionManager**: `mockSessionManager` with configurable `getFunc`\n361: 4. **Mock Logger**: `MockLogger` with Info/Error recording for middleware tests\n362: \n363: ### Integration Test Scenarios\n364: \n365: | Scenario | Description |\n366: |----------|-------------|\n367: | Full request flow | Client → Router → mock WorkloadMgr → verify proxy headers |\n368: | Session reuse | Provide existing sessionID → verify no new sandbox created |\n369: | New session creation | Empty sessionID → verify POST to WorkloadMgr, store write |\n370: | TLS startup | EnableTLS=true with missing cert → verify error |\n371: | Graceful shutdown | Context cancellation → verify 10s timeout shutdown |\n372: \n373: ---\n374: \n375: ## Validation Checklist\n376: \n377: - [ ] `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable required for SessionManager initialization\n378: - [ ] Concurrency limit defaults to 1000 when `MaxConcurrentRequests <= 0`\n379: - [ ] JWT expires in 5 minutes, signed with RS256\n380: - [ ] Session activity updated before and after proxy for accurate idle tracking\n381: - [ ] Entry point selection uses prefix match, falls back to first entry\n382: - [ ] Proxy error classification based on error message content\n383: - [ ] Health check `/health/ready` returns 503 when SessionManager unavailable\n384: - [ ] Gin mode set to ReleaseMode when `config.Debug=false`\n385: \n386: ---\n387: \n388: ## Open Questions\n389: \n390: 1. Should JWT key persistence be mandatory for production deployments (current implementation allows ephemeral keys)?\n391: 2. Should proxy timeout be configurable per entry point (currently hardcoded in transport)?\n392: 3. Should session creation be rate-limited independently from concurrent request limit?\n393: \n394: ---\n395: \n396: ## References\n397: \n398: - `session-routing/design.md` — Session routing module design\n399: - `pkg/router/doc.go` — Interface definitions\n400: - `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` — SandboxInfo and request/response types\n401: - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` — Labels, annotations, condition constants\n402: - `deployment/client-go.md` — Kubernetes client library reference\n\n(End of file - total 402 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-010 — Router 会话管理 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-010 — Router 会话管理 |\n| Module | `pkg/router` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nThe Router module provides HTTP-based session routing for AgentCube sandboxes. It manages session lifecycle, routes incoming invocation requests to appropriate sandbox pods via reverse proxy, and handles JWT-based authentication for secure communication between Router and Workload Manager.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### System Context\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-010/design.md","time":{"start":1775851879377,"end":1775851879390}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851879396,"sessionID":"ses_286fb3a50ffevXBFaIE185eANl","part":{"id":"prt_d79053bbe001RlgOB5ibR6h0Yo","messageID":"msg_d790513b70017BHPjMM1eOOInL","sessionID":"ses_286fb3a50ffevXBFaIE185eANl","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-035b6aa88606492689652f4047ca5788","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-010/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-010/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-010 — Router 会话管理 Proposal\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Implement session management for the AgentCube Router component. This provides the core session resolution and sandbox creation logic that enables session-aware routing. The session management component:\n6: \n7: 1. **Session Resolution**: Reads `x-agentcube-session-id` header, looks up existing `SandboxInfo` from the Store when present\n8: 2. **Sandbox Creation**: When session ID is empty, creates new sandboxes via Workload Manager HTTP API\n9: 3. **Response Validation**: Parses `CreateSandboxResponse` from Workload Manager and builds in-memory `SandboxInfo` with session metadata\n10: 4. **Store Integration**: Persists sandbox info to Store after successful creation for subsequent session lookups\n11: 5. **Error Handling**: Maps Workload Manager errors to Router-specific error types (NotFound, Timeout, etc.)\n12: 6. **Service Account Auth**: Attaches Kubernetes service account token for in-cluster Workload Manager authentication\n13: \n14: ## Scope\n15: \n16: ### In Scope\n17: \n18: | Deliverable | Description |\n19: |-------------|-------------|\n20: | `pkg/router/session_manager.go` | SessionManager interface implementation with GetSandboxBySession, createSandbox logic |\n21: | `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go` | Unit tests for session resolution, sandbox creation, error handling, HTTP client behavior |\n22: | `pkg/router/doc.go` | SessionManager interface definition, Store interface, Logger interface |\n23: | `pkg/router/errors.go` | SessionNotFoundError, WorkloadManagerError types with APIStatus implementation |\n24: | Environment configuration | WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL required, optional service account token reading |\n25: | HTTP client setup | Timeout 2m, MaxIdleConnsPerHost 100, HTTP2 transport configuration |\n26: \n27: ### Key Components\n28: \n29: ```\n30: pkg/router/\n31: ├── SessionManager (doc.go)\n32: │   ├── Interface: GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)\n33: │   ├── Dependencies: Store (for sandbox lookup/storage), Workload Manager HTTP client\n34: │   └── Lifecycle: NewSessionManager validates WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL, builds HTTP client\n35: │\n36: ├── sessionManager struct (session_manager.go)\n37: │   ├── storeClient: Store interface implementation\n38: │   ├── workloadMgrAddr: Workload Manager service URL\n39: │   ├── httpClient: *http.Client with HTTP2, 2m timeout, 100 idle conns\n40: │   └── GetSandboxBySession: sessionID empty → createSandbox, else → store lookup\n41: │\n42: ├── createSandbox (session_manager.go)\n43: │   ├── Validate CreateSandboxRequest (kind, namespace, name)\n44: │   ├── Route by kind: AgentRuntime → /v1/agent-runtime, CodeInterpreter → /v1/code-interpreter\n45: │   ├── POST JSON request to Workload Manager\n46: │   ├── Attach Authorization header with SA token if available\n47: │   ├── Parse CreateSandboxResponse (SessionID, SandboxID, SandboxName, EntryPoints)\n48: │   ├── Build SandboxInfo with default expiresAt (30m), status \"Running\"\n49: │   └── Store to Store via StoreSandbox\n50: │\n51: └── Errors (errors.go)\n52:     ├── SessionNotFoundError: sessionID not found in store → 404\n53:     ├── WorkloadManagerError: HTTP error from WM → StatusCode + Msg\n54:     └── readServiceAccountToken: /var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\n55: ```\n56: \n57: ### Out of Scope\n58: \n59: - Reverse proxy implementation (covered by AR-009)\n60: - JWT token generation (covered by AR-009)\n61: - Concurrency limiting middleware (covered by AR-009)\n62: - Health endpoint handlers (covered by AR-009)\n63: - Store implementation details (covered by session-store spec)\n64: - Workload Manager implementation (covered by AR-006, AR-007)\n65: - Distributed session cache (Redis-based)\n66: - Session eviction/cleanup (covered by AR-008 GC)\n67: \n68: ## Impact Analysis\n69: \n70: ### Upstream Dependencies\n71: \n72: | Dependency | Impact |\n73: |------------|--------|\n74: | `pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response, kind constants (AgentRuntimeKind, CodeInterpreterKind) |\n75: | `pkg/router/doc.go` | Store interface (GetSandboxBySessionID, StoreSandbox), Logger interface |\n76: | `os.Getenv` | WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL required at construction |\n77: | `os.ReadFile` | Service account token from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` |\n78: | `golang.org/x/net/http2` | HTTP2 transport configuration for Workload Manager client |\n79: | Workload Manager service | POST `/v1/agent-runtime`, `/v1/code-interpreter` endpoints |\n80: \n81: ### Downstream Consumers\n82: \n83: | Consumer | Usage |\n84: |----------|-------|\n85: | `Server.handleInvoke` | Calls GetSandboxBySession to resolve sandbox for proxy routing |\n86: | `Server.handleHealthReady` | Checks sessionManager nil for readiness probe |\n87: | Store implementations | Receives StoreSandbox calls after creation |\n88: | Workload Manager | Receives sandbox creation requests |\n89: | Reverse proxy | Uses SandboxInfo.EntryPoints for target URL selection |\n90: \n91: ### Breaking Change Considerations\n92: \n93: - **Session Header Name**: `x-agentcube-session-id` header is client contract; changing requires all clients to update\n94: - **Workload Manager URL**: Environment variable `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` must be set; startup fails if missing\n95: - **Kind Routing**: `/v1/agent-runtime` and `/v1/code-interpreter` paths are fixed contracts with Workload Manager\n96: - **Response Schema**: `CreateSandboxResponse` fields (sessionId, sandboxId, sandboxName, entryPoints) must be provided\n97: - **Default Expiry**: 30-minute default `ExpiresAt` affects sandbox lifecycle\n98: \n99: ## Alternatives Considered\n100: \n101: ### Alternative 1: Direct Kubernetes API Lookup\n102: \n103: **Approach**: Session manager directly queries Kubernetes API for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter CRs instead of delegating to Workload Manager.\n104: \n105: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n106: |--------|------------|\n107: | Pros | No intermediate service; direct CR access; simpler architecture |\n108: | Cons | Router requires K8s client permissions; no sandbox pod endpoint resolution; no entry point mapping |\n109: \n110: **Decision**: Rejected. Workload Manager handles CR creation AND pod endpoint resolution (EntryPoints). Router needs pod addresses for proxying, not just CR status.\n111: \n112: ### Alternative 2: Session Cache in Router Memory\n113: \n114: **Approach**: Cache sandbox info in router process memory without Store dependency.\n115: \n116: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n117: |--------|------------|\n118: | Pros | Zero latency for lookups; no external store dependency |\n119: | Cons | Lost on router restart; no persistence; cannot share across router instances |\n120: \n121: **Decision**: Rejected. Store provides persistence across router restarts and enables idle timeout detection by GC component. Memory-only cache breaks session continuity.\n122: \n123: ### Alternative 3: Session ID Embedded in URL Path\n124: \n125: **Approach**: Include session ID in URL path like `/v1/sessions/:sessionId/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path`.\n126: \n127: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n128: |--------|------------|\n129: | Pros | Session visible in URL; no header dependency |\n130: | Cons | Breaks logical resource routing (namespace/name pattern); clients must track session IDs; URL pollution |\n131: \n132: **Decision**: Rejected. Header-based session ID (`x-agentcube-session-id`) allows clients to use logical names (namespace/name) while Router handles session state internally. This matches OpenAI-style API design.\n133: \n134: ### Alternative 4: No Session Creation on Router\n135: \n136: **Approach**: Router never creates sandboxes; clients must call Workload Manager directly for session creation.\n137: \n138: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n139: |--------|------------|\n140: | Pros | Router simpler; no Workload Manager client code |\n141: | Cons | Clients manage session lifecycle; two-step flow (create then invoke); no session abstraction benefit |\n142: \n143: **Decision**: Rejected. Session creation on first invocation (empty session ID) is core AgentCube design—clients use single invoke endpoint, Router handles creation transparently.\n144: \n145: ### Alternative 5: gRPC for Workload Manager Communication\n146: \n147: **Approach**: Use gRPC instead of HTTP for Workload Manager sandbox creation.\n148: \n149: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n150: |--------|------------|\n151: | Pros | Better performance; streaming support; typed contracts |\n152: | Cons | Requires gRPC service on Workload Manager; incompatible with HTTP-only deployment; adds protobuf dependency |\n153: \n154: **Decision**: Rejected. HTTP/JSON API aligns with Kubernetes ecosystem and REST API conventions. Both Router and Workload Manager already use HTTP stack (Gin, net/http).\n155: \n156: ## Risks\n157: \n158: | Risk | Mitigation |\n159: |------|------------|\n160: | Workload Manager unavailable | Startup fails with explicit error if WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL missing; HTTP client timeout 2m |\n161: | Workload Manager returns non-OK | WorkloadManagerError captures status code + body for debugging |\n162: | Empty SessionID in response | Validation returns error \"empty sessionId in response\" |\n163: | Store lookup fails | SessionNotFoundError with sessionID in error message |\n164: | Service account token unavailable | Optional; gracefully skipped if file doesn't exist |\n165: | Sandbox creation race (duplicate session) | Workload Manager handles deduplication; StoreSandbox may overwrite |\n166: | HTTP2 connection issues | ConfigureTransport with ReadIdleTimeout, PingTimeout for connection health |\n167: | Request body unmarshal failure | Error wrapped with context \"failed to parse response\" |\n168: \n169: ## Implementation Notes\n170: \n171: 1. **Environment Variables**: `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` (required), reads from `os.Getenv`\n172: 2. **HTTP Client**: Timeout 2 minutes, MaxIdleConnsPerHost 100, HTTP2 via `http2.ConfigureTransport`\n173: 3. **Service Account Token**: Path `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`, trimmed before use\n174: 4. **Default Namespace**: `IdentityNamespace = \"default\"` or from `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env\n175: 5. **Request Validation**: `CreateSandboxRequest.Validate()` checks kind, namespace, name\n176: 6. **Endpoint Routing**: AgentRuntimeKind → `/v1/agent-runtime`, CodeInterpreterKind → `/v1/code-interpreter`\n177: 7. **Default Expiry**: `ExpiresAt = time.Now().Add(30 * time.Minute)` for new sandboxes\n178: 8. **Store Integration**: `StoreSandbox` called after successful creation; store handles persistence\n179: 9. **Error Types**: `SessionNotFoundError`, `WorkloadManagerError` implement `APIStatus` interface\n180: \n181: ## References\n182: \n183: - `session-routing/spec.md` - Full requirement specification\n184: - `pkg/router/session_manager.go` - Implementation\n185: - `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go` - Test coverage\n186: - `pkg/router/doc.go` - Interface definitions\n187: - `pkg/router/errors.go` - Error types\n188: - `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` - SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response\n189: - `deployment/client-go.md` - Kubernetes client reference\n190: - `changes/AR-009/proposal.md` - Related Router HTTP reverse proxy proposal\n\n(End of file - total 190 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-010 — Router 会话管理 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement session management for the AgentCube Router component. This provides the core session resolution and sandbox creation logic that enables session-aware routing. The session management component:\n\n1. **Session Resolution**: Reads `x-agentcube-session-id` header, looks up existing `SandboxInfo` from the Store when present\n2. **Sandbox Creation**: When session ID is empty, creates new sandboxes via Workload Manager HTTP API\n3. **Response Validation**: Parses `CreateSandboxResponse` from Workload Manager and builds in-memory `SandboxInfo` with session metadata\n4. **Store Integration**: Persists sandbox info to Store after successful creation for subsequent session lookups\n5. **Error Handling**: Maps Workload Manager errors to Router-specific error types (NotFound, Timeout, etc.)\n6. **Service Account Auth**: Attaches Kubernetes service account token for in-cluster Workload Manager authentication\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/router/session_manager.go` | SessionManager interface implementation with GetSandboxBySession, createSandbox logic |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-010/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775851879381,"end":1775851879393}}}}
